# Docker rebuild (this repo)

When you change anything that affects the running container image or Compose stack—`Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`, `.dockerignore`, `requirements.txt`, `app/`, or `static/`—finish the task by running from the project root:

```bash
docker compose build
```

If the user is running the stack and needs the new image applied, follow with:

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

Do not wait for the user to ask for a rebuild; run the build (and `up -d` when appropriate) as part of the same turn unless they are in ask-only mode or Docker is unavailable.
